column5: managed to boat a football of a brown today in the st.lawrence river...  6.15lbs and 22 inches long
nice fish, it's been eating pretty well, were you fishing for Browns? I'm guessing no
Beauty fish man!  Thanks for sharing,  MTBF

actualy i was...  my friends have been catching them for years off shore...  so today i took my f150 to the launch and busted up the ice with my tires and ruturned in 30 minutes with my boat to try this rare st.lawrence trout experience and within 10 minutes my partner said he hit a rock with his lure... then i couldnt believe it when i saw a nice brown chasing his spoon to the boat!!!  an hour or so later i caught one right were he had missed the fish earlier...
oh yeah... it was stuffed to the gills with minnows and GOBIES!
cool, I didn't know there was many in there, nice fish
Nice Fish. Can't wait to get out to Lake Ontario to get some fishing in soon.
Nice fat brown!  Congrats on your first!
